<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Navy To Acquire 12 Patrol Craft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2901144894 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2901144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Republic of Singapore Navy is to acquire 12 new 
patrol craft to replace 12 coastal patrol craft that have served 
the Navy since 1980's. The second minister for defense, Dr. Lee 
Boon Yang, said the new patrol craft will be equiped with 
state-of-the-art command, control, and communications system. 
They will further enhance the Navy's fighting and civil defense 
capabilities. 
  Dr. Lee said for the first time in Singapore Navy's 
shipbuilding program, all the phases of design, construction, 
and system integration are carried out locally. The patrol 
vessels will be designed and built by the Singapore Shipbuilding 
and Engineering, a subsidiary of Singapore Technology. Dr. Lee 
was speaking at the launch of the Navy's second mine 
counter-measure vessel, RSS [Republic of Singapore Ship] (Kalau) 
at the Singapore Shipbuilding and Engineering yard at Tuas. The 
vessel is one of the four mine counter-measure vessels Singapore 
has ordered from Sweden. 

</TEXT>

