<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chea Sim Comments on Khmer Rouge Position </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101104294 Phnom Penh AKP in English 1000 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK3101104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP January 31 -- Acting State President 
and Chairman of National Assembly Chea Sim said that the Khmer 
Rouge had not showed its fair attitude towards national 
reconciliation. 
  During a meeting with representative of Canadian diplomatic 
mission to Cambodia David Martin Colagott, Samdech Chea Sim said 
the faction still refused to recognise the Royal Government of 
Cambodia and conditions proposed by King Norodom Sihanouk on 
cease-fire, the faction's troops demobilisation and integration 
into the royal army, and the return of its controlled areas of 
Pailin and Preah Vihear to the royal government. 
  He also told the Canadian diplomat that the Khmer Rouge also 
increased its strategy in order regain power in the country. 
  The acting state president also expressed thanks to the 
Canadian government for its efforts and assistance to the peace 
process and national reconstruction of Cambodia. 
  For his part, David Martin expressed pleasure over the unity 
between the two main parties of FUNCINPEC [National United Front 
for an Independent, Neutral, Peaceful, and Cooperative Cambodia] 
and the CPP [Cambodian People's Party] in the government, 
stressing that it was the firm aspiration for Cambodians. 

</TEXT>

