<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khmer Rouge Claim Tanks Captured at Sre Noy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3001085594 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3001085594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Vietnamese communist puppets on 26 January sent 
out more than 200 troops backed by seven tanks to invade a 
liberated area north of Sre Noy [in Oddar Meanchey Province]. 
The people and the National Army of Democratic Kampuchea 
ambushed them with mines and attacked them with heavy guns on 
the stretch of road at Prey S'at, killing 12 enemy soldiers and 
wounding many others. We also seized a significant quantity of 
firearms and ammunition and captured two tanks -- one about to 
run out of gas and the other about to break down. The enemy 
ground troops and the other five tanks hastily retreated behind 
their lines. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

