<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   VGNUFC on Initial Result of Samraong Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2801063194 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2801063194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on results of the people's attack which destroyed </F>
Samraong, the seat of Oddar Meanchey Province] 
  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] Over 2,000 people were 
divided into groups to attack the Vietnamese communist puppet 
administrators and ringleaders from the western part of Samraong 
District along Route 69. They attacked and destroyed the police 
post and the site of an army engineering unit, which was in 
charge of preparing the way for suppressive operations. Another 
group of the people's forces attacked an artillery position at 
Don Ken village south of Samraong District hall. Another group 
attacked the central area, totally destroying the Oddar Meanchey 
provincial hall, the provincial seat, and Samraong District 
hall. Another group attacked the camps of the Vietnamese 
communist puppets at O Russei, destroying two positions 
belonging to the 286th Division and Nhoek Bunchhai's forces. 
Another group attacked positions in the suburban area, totally 
destroying the positions at Bos Sbouv and Trabek. 
  All groups in this people's attack linked up at Samraong 
market and occupied this area for over 3 hours. The people's 
forces destroyed the puppets' heavy military machines which were 
being used for building roads for their military trucks, as well 
as armored personnel carriers and tanks used for launching 
operations in the eastern and western parts of Route 68. They 
destroyed three [words indistinct], five [words indistinct] 
tractors, four ten-wheeled and thirteen-wheeled trucks, an oil 
truck, a water truck, two ammunition depots, two 122-mm and B-30 
cannon, three 82-mm mortars, four 12.7 guns, and two DK-75 guns. 
They also killed 36 of the enemy on the spot and wounded over 60 
others. [passage omitted]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

