<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   VGNUFC Reports Attack on Stoung Market </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2801034194 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2801034194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] On the night of 25 January, the 
people and the National Army of Democratic Kampuchea [NADK] took 
the initiative in attacking the Vietnamese communist puppet 
stronghold in Stoung District, Kompong Thom Province. The 
people believe that this bridgehead should be burned to prevent 
them from attacking us. Before midnight on 25 January, the 
people and the NADK surrounded and attacked the Stoung District 
township. After an hour of fighting, we had completely occupied 
the district market and destroyed the district office buildings, 
two barracks, a police quarters, six vehicles and armored 
carriers, and a rice warehouse. We killed seven cruel district 
officials; four puppet officers holding the rank of colonel, 
major, and captain; and 12 invading enemy soldiers. We also 
wounded a number of enemy soldiers and captured 38 others. The 
other puppet troops quickly fled for their lives from the Stoung 
District township. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

