<H3> <TI>   Khmer Rouge: 68 Ampil Villages Liberated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2901111994 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2901111994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In January 1994, the people in Ampil District of 
Oddar Meanchey Province launched attacks to liberate their 
villages and communes from the Vietnamese communist puppets and 
the U.S. puppets, who jointly invaded and seized the district in 
August 1993. 
  Since the beginning of January, the National Army of 
Democratic Kampuchea joined forces with the people to mount 
attacks and liberated 68 villages in the area from Route 68 to 
the west [words indistinct], from Ampil to Phnum Srok, and from 
Phnum Srok to Banteay Chhmar. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

