<H3> <TI>   ROK Organization Denounces Patriot Deployment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3001084594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0834 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3001084594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 30 (KCNA) -- The Pusan Alliance 
for Democracy and National Reunification released a statement 
Saturday denouncing the United States and the South Korean 
puppet clique for scheming to deploy Patriot missiles in South 
Korea, according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  The statement said that "the U.S. projected deployment of 
Patriot missiles may make difficult the negotiations between the 
North and the International Atomic Energy Agency on nuclear 
inspection and lead to a war." 
  It said that "the plan is entirely contradictory to the 
universal trend toward peace and reconciliation" and urged its 
immediate withdrawal. 
  The organisation strongly demanded that the South Korean 
puppet authorities refuse introducing missiles which will bring 
the situation of the Korean peninsula to the brink of war. 

</TEXT>

