<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam's Remarks to Business Groups Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3101054994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0523 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3101054994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Crafty Sermon for Crackdown on Labor Movement" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- The traitor Kim 
Yong-sam told chairmen of comprador groups at "Chongwadae" a few 
days ago that "trinity" of the "government," the employers and 
workers should be established for "the increase of international 
competitiveness." 
  NODONG SINMUN today brands the "trinity" as a slogan of the 
puppet authorities and comprador entrepreneurs to crack down on 
the workers' struggle for wage hike and vital rights under the 
pretext of "economic stability" and "increase of 
competitiveness." 
  The news analyst says: 
  That day the traitor Kim Yong-sam preached "labor-management 
harmony", saying rather "humane treatment" is necessary than 
wage hike in order to make this year "the first year free from 
labor-management disputes." This is quite ill-intentioned. 
  By "labor-management harmony" he meant that the workers must 
refrain from any demand and any protest but meekly yield to the 
exploitation by the employers. 
  Kim Yong-sam told the businessmen that he would loosen the 
"regulations" obstructive to business activities to the extent 
that the employers are satisfied. 
  Although Kim Yong-sam wants the workers to work silently 
without protesting to the "government" and the employers, it is 
a futile dream. 
  The South Korean workers and people will not be cheated by 
the traitor's sermon on "labor-management harmony" and "trinity" 
but rise up courageously in the struggle to overthrow the 
"civilian"-veiled regime. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

