<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Religious Leader Billy Graham Continues Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Kim Il-song 29 Jan </H4>
<F P=102> SK2901094794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0900 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2901094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0900 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song met with a 
U.S. religious leader and his party. On 29 January, the great 
leader Comrade Kim Il-song met with U.S. religious leader Rev. 
Billy Graham and his party who are visiting our country. 
  Kim Yong-nam, vice premier and foreign minister; Kang 
Yong-sop, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean 
Christian Federation; and Chong Chae-chol, chairman of the 
Central Committee of the Korea Catholics Association were 
present. 
  During the meeting the U.S. religious leader conveyed U.S. 
President Bill Clinton's verbal message to the great leader 
Comrade Kim Il-song. The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song 
conversed with the guests in a warm and friendly atmosphere. 
The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song hosted a luncheon for the 
guests. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

