<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Sends Thanks to Working People </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3101061294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0502 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3101061294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il sent thanks to the working people who have 
done good things for society and collective. 
  37 family members of the officials of the cooperative farm 
management committee of Kowon County, South Hamgyong Province, 
formed a work team last year for an active assistance to the 
socialist countryside. They have increased the yield of maize 
per hectare by doing well farming as demanded by the chuche 
farming method in 10 hectares of maize fields of a cooperative 
farm. 
  Choe Kum-sik, curator of the library of the Kang Pan-sok 
University for the bereaved children of revolutionaries, has 
contributed her all to rearing children as the reliable 
successors of the revolution, the national cadres, over the 
past forty years. 
  Yun Myong-suk and Cha Kyong-hui who are cleaners of 
Pyongyang-Nampo highway showed the fine spiritual and moral 
traits of the Korean youths by giving back the things dropped by 
foreigners. 
  At the meetings conveying the thanks, speakers said the 
thanks contained warm love and trust of the dear leader who even 
values and estimates humble things done by revolutionary 
soldiers. 

</TEXT>

