<H3> <TI>   Article on Communist Movement Advancement Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3001102694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1003 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3001102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 29 [date as received] (KCNA) -- 
The international communist movement made further advance in 
1993 through powerful political activities and struggle to 
tighten the bonds of solidarity, declared international 
secretary of the Brazilian Communist Party Jose Reinaldo 
Carvalho in an article titled "Advance of Communist Movement" 
published in the party organ A CLASE OPERARIA. 
  He said the anti-imperialist and democratic progressive 
forces got united in one idea at various meetings and took the 
initiative with a great influence worldwide. 
  The declaration "Let us defend and advance the cause of 
socialism" adopted in Pyongyang in April 1992 has been signed by 
more than 200 communist and workers' parties and other 
revolutionary and progressive parties, he said. 
  "Our fighting task is to strengthen the solidarity of 
communist and workers' parties and the anti-imperialist, 
progressive forces worldwide, actively support socialist 
countries and unite with the peoples of the nations fighting for 
democracy and national independence," he stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

