<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Innovations in Technology Proposals Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901110794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1032 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The "April 15 
technical innovation shock brigades" of Korea have introduced 
more than 140,000 technical innovation proposals over the last 
one year, actively contributing to the chuche orientation, 
modernization and scientization of the national economy. And 
they helped save 45,000 tons of steel, 407,000 tons of coal, 
30,000 tons of oil and large quantities of other fuel and 
materials, as well as workforce and fund. 
  In this period 1,830 units including 67 factories have 
received the title of model technical innovation factory 
(workshop or workteam). Two factories of them have received the 
title twice. 
  The technical innovation shock brigades were organised at 
industrial establishments from 1980. They include local skilled 
workers and technicians. They solve technical problems in 
production and construction, thus contributing to the economic 
development of the nation. 

</TEXT>

