<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rengo Head: Murayama Resignation Unnecessary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3001083594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 Jan 
94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3001083594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the afternoon of 29 January, Japanese Trade 
Union Confederation [Rengo] chairman Akira Yamagishi held a news 
conference at Rengo headquarters. Following enactment of the 
political reform bills, Yamagishi noted the resignation of 
chairman Tomiichi Murayama and other executives of the Social 
Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] is unnecessary. He said: "The 
responsibility (for the upper house's rejection of the bills) 
should be assumed by SDPJ rebels, but not the party leadership." 

</TEXT>

