<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Counterintelligence Head Makes Threats </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2701011494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 2247 GMT 26 Jan 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2701011494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 26 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
former chief of the counterintelligence Colonel L. Sanjaasuren 
has notified the chairman and the vice chairman of the 
parliament and the prime minister that in case these high 
officials not made clear conclusions he is ready to make public 
new facts telling about their involvement in corruption and 
contacts with secret services of some foreign states. In this 
way the former chief of the counterintelligence who has been 
removed recently from the office expressed his readiness to 
complete "the case." L. Sanjaasuren started from fact than at 
the end of the last year he has held a press conference at which 
he informed that there are materials documents in his department 
telling about possible contacts of the above mentioned high 
officials with foreign secret services. The parliament working 
group on investigation of this information has not revealed any 
signs telling about liquidation of these materials as L. 
Sanjaasuren supposed in this connection. Colonel L. Sanjaasuren 
had to announce that a special system of concealing improper 
deeds of state high officials is already formed in the country. 
As far as the parliament speaker N. Bagadandi, vice speaker J. 
Gombojav, and the Prime Minister P. Jasray are concerned they 
are resolutely rejecting the charges of L. Sanjaasuren and the 
press. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

