Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  31 January 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Helicopter Landing Case Investigated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2701011394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 2248 GMT 26 Jan 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2701011394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 26 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
newspaper ARDYN ERH publishes an article by its correspondent 
trying to clear up the circumstances around the scandalous case 
with an "Mi-8" helicopter with 27005 number on its board. 
  The helicopter crossed illegally the Mongolian frontier 
bordering on the Russian Federation on June 28 and up to now is 
on the Buyant-Uhaa Airport. 
  According to a competent officer of the investigating board 
under the Central Police Department by August 20 the general 
board on ensuring state security by its former name had 
instituted proceedings in connection with the helicopter and 
carried out proper investigations. It was found that pilots of 
the helicopter had returned home after taking it to Mongolia. 
The other day Deputy Director of the Russian "Godli" firm B. B. 
Gomboyev came to Ulaanbaatar with the purpose of receiving money 
for the helicopter having been sold to the Mongolian "Oyuny 
Undraa" firm. In response to it we have demanded to send here 
their pilots having violated the law of the country, he said. 
  According to him, the Mongolian "Oyuny Undraa" firm did not 
purchase the helicopter for itself but played only the role of a 
mediator in the selling of the helicopter. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-48894 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas020_j_94002" </HT>


