<H3> <TI>   Official Dismisses Reports of Taiwan Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2801135094 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2801135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Reports that ASEAN will hold economic talks with 
Taiwan have been dismissed as untrue. In a press statement 
issued in Jakarta today, ASEAN Secretary General Datuk Ajit 
Singh said ASEAN has no plan to hold any official talks with 
Taiwan. The ASEAN secretary general stressed that it is normal 
for ASEAN businessmen to hold consultations with third parties 
at international meetings. In this connection, Datuk Ajit Singh 
said ASEAN officials may hold hold informal talks with Taiwanese 
counterparts at an APEC [Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation] 
meeting in Jakarta at the end of this month. 

</TEXT>

