<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Signs Agreement, Departs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101094094 Vientiane KPL in English 0756 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK3101094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, January 31 (KPL) -- The Foreign 
Relations Board of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party Central 
Committee, on January 30, signed with the Foreign Relations 
Board of the Communist Party of Vietnam Central Committee a 
cooperation agreement between the two boards for 1994. 
  Signing the agreement were foreign minister Somsavat 
Lengsavat, who is deputy head of the Party CC [Central 
Committee] Foreign Relations Board of Laos, and Mr. Do Vanh Tai, 
deputy head of the Party CC Foreign Relations Board of Vietnam. 
  The cooperation agreement provides that the Vietnamese side 
will give assistance in expertise through the party channel to 
the Lao side. It also will help train some more political staff 
for Laos. 
  Mr. Do Vanh Tai and his delegation left here for home in the 
afternoon of the same day, ending a week-long visit to Lao PDR 
[Lao People's Democratic Republic]. 

</TEXT>

