<H3> <TI>   Berov Urges People To Unite, Thanks Cabinet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3012210993 Sofia BTA in English 1934 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> AU3012210993 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, December 30 (BTA) -- A prime-time address by 
Prime Minister Berov called upon Bulgarian people to unite. 
"Society is tired of political strife and wants a calmer life 
and more common sense," the prime minister said. "I will not 
promise you a bright future, but as a nation and a state, we 
have to break clear from our past," he went on to say. 
According to Prof. Berov, the National Assembly bears inscribed 
the secret for Bulgaria's headway: "Unity Is Strength." 
  Prime Minister Berov summed up the 1993 performance of the 
government which he headed precisely an year ago. He thanked 
the cabinet, which he called "valiant," for its "courage, zeal 
and wisdom." 
  "We worked to further advance the changes that had already 
been launched though there was nobody to applaud us. We did 
everything we could to take this country's ship into calmer 
waters," Prime Minister Berov said. 

</TEXT>

