<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From BTA's 3 December "Press Review"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Sofia, January 3 (BTA) -- [passage omitted] For 
the time being, Ukraine has declined Bulgaria's offer to barter 
coal for electricity, the 24 CHASA daily reports, quoting the 
chief of the Power Engineering Committee Nikita Shervashidze who 
returned from Ukraine at the end of December. Bulgaria will 
start buying coal at considerably higher prices from the 
Republic of South Africa which would most probably raise the 
prices of electricity, Mr. Shervashidze believes. He says that 
the possibilities for setting up a new common power grid among 
Bulgaria, Greece, Slovenia, Croatia, Romania, Serbia and Ukraine 
were discussed in Kiev. Negotiations with Ukraine will continue 
two weeks later, during a visit to Kiev of a Bulgarian 
delegation led by Deputy Prime Minister Valentin Karabashev, the 
private daily STANDART NEWS reports. A commentary in the same 
newspaper says that if the National Electricity Company were 
private, the negotiations would definitely succeed. [passage 
omitted] 

