<H3> <TI>   Status of Kozloduy Nuclear Reactors Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3012144693 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1400 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> AU3012144693 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After a complex and comprehensive inspection, the 
State Receiving Committee signed Act 16 with which the 
1000-megawatt sixth reactor of the Kozloduy Nuclear Power Plant 
has been accepted as suitable for regular functioning. 
  The sixth reactor is now functioning at full capacity. The 
other two reactors -- the second and the fourth -- are also 
functioning at full capacity. The capacity of the 440-megawatt 
first reactor is constantly being increased on the basis of 
tests that are being constantly conducted. At the beginning of 
the week, that reactor was connected to the country's power grid. 
  The 1000-megawatt fifth reactor has been switched off for 
repairs and refueling. It is expected that this reactor will be 
connected to the power grid by the end of January 1994. 

</TEXT>

