<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statistics Bureau Notes Dec Inflation Rate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012162093 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1554 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012162093 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, Dec 30 (TANJUG) -- Inflation in Yugoslavia 
in December alone will stand at one million percent, the Federal 
Bureau of Statistics said on Thursday [30 December]. Retail 
prices will be 1,790 times higher than in November, and living 
expenses will increase 2,839 times. 
  The draconic sanctions which the U.N. Security Council 
imposed on Yugoslavia in late May of 1992 have resulted in 
severe shortages of goods, a monetary chaos and general 
impoverishment of Yugoslavs the majority of whom now live on a 
subsistence level. 

</TEXT>

