<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government `Disgusted' With RFE Broadcasting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012205693 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 2000 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3012205693 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak Government is disgusted with RFE 
broadcasting. This is what RFE Director Robert Gillette said in 
Bratislava today, adding that this is the real reason for the 
Slovak side's termination of the agreement with RFE. 
  According to Transport and Communications Minister Roman 
Hofbauer and Culture Minister Dusan Svobodnik, whom Director 
Gillette met, RFE broadcasting is biased and is directed against 
the Slovak Government. Gillette said that this was 
unsubstantiated and added that the RFE hoped to reverse the 
Slovak side's decision and conclude an agreement at the next 
meeting scheduled for the end of January. 

</TEXT>

