<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak Stresses Importance of NATO Links </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301122394 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1105 
GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0301122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The government's most important tasks concern 
the economy, declared Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak during this 
morning's conversation with listeners and journalists of Polish 
Radio's First Program. [passage omitted] 
  One of the important subjects broached during the 
conversation with Prime Minister Pawlak was the possibility of 
Poland joining the economic and defense structures of the West. 
  [Begin Pawlak recording] This is not just a case of our 
expectations and our choice -- it is also a case of the decision 
and the responsibility of European and other countries that make 
up the NATO structure. I think it is in our common interest 
that the changes that took place in 1989 should find a very 
definite expression in these joint interrelations -- both 
economic ones and those connected with external security -- in 
order that we might calmly be able to say that this was not just 
a short breath of freedom before having to cope with the same 
problems that we have had to deal with for such a long time. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

