<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Striking Miners Reach Agreement With Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112084393 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0100 
GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112084393 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the striking workforce of the 
barite colliery in Boguszow have reached an agreement with the 
government that makes it possible for the strike to be suspended 
or broken off. The state budget will give 12 billion zlotys to 
the Fund for the Walbrzych Area so that the mine can operate for 
three more months. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-48962 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu001_p_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-001 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  3 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

