<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajisnik: `No Further Concessions' to Muslims </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112152393 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1355 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112152393 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Obrenovac, 31 Dec (TANJUG) -- Momcilo Krajisnik, 
president of the Assembly of the republic of Srpska, has said 
that this year the Serbs of the republic of Srpska have been 
carrying out the difficult task of fighting the entire world to 
save their state, their dignity, and their freedom. In this 
difficult struggle we have managed, along with all the other 
Serbs who have been vilified for demonstrating solidarity with 
us, to resist all the pressures which fundamentally aimed to 
bring about Serbian divisions and rifts, Krajisnik said. 
  Krajisnik maintains that there has been no justice or law in 
all these assaults on us, something that is best borne out by 
the European Union [EU] stands, as it in fact encouraged the 
Muslims to first gain a foothold in central Bosnia and then to 
take on the Serbs in the spring. We will, of course, be ready 
for them, Krajisnik cautioned. 
  Asked by a Obrenovac radio reporter whether a change in the 
leadership of Herceg-Bosna would tilt the balance of forces on 
the ground, Mr. Krajisnik said that the possibility of Mate 
Boban being replaced by Akmadzic would result in better 
relations between the Croats and Muslims, something that in its 
turn would not bring about changes to the Serbian negotiating 
position. "All the more so since neither of them takes any 
steps, as this is done by Mr. Tudjman, the Catholic Church and 
the Vatican. In any case, as far as the Muslims are concerned, 
there will be no further concessions, as it has already been 
proved that they cannot reach their goal. Concessions in 
western or eastern Bosnia would jeopardize the continuity of the 
republic of Srpska," Krajisnik said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

