<H3> <TI>   UN Sarajevo Headquarters Hit by Shell </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0101133394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0101133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last night, 15 minutes after midnight, a shell fired 
from a Serbian position hit the PTT Engineering building, the 
Sarajevo headquarters of UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces], UN 
Major Manuel Capea told the Bosnia-Herzegovina press. The shell 
hit the duty-free shop and slightly damaged the news conference 
hall. 
  Yesterday, throughout the day, the aggressor fired 54 shells 
at the city. During the night another 93 shells landed on the 
city. This morning there were bouts of intense sniper fire. 
According to UNPROFOR, yesterday five Sarajevans were killed 
and 40 wounded. 
  The people of Sarajevo welcomed 1994 without water and 
electricity. 

</TEXT>

