<H3> <TI>   Muslims Report Croat Attacks on Mostar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0101203294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0101203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two people were killed and six wounded in the free 
part of Mostar in last night's large-caliber artillery attacks 
from Croatian Army and HVO [Croatian Defense Council] positions, 
the 4th Corps press center reports. 
  Today the ustashas directed most of their attacks on Blagaj, 
targeting it with more than 100 destructive shells and causing 
fresh casualties and considerable material damage. This town, 
which is also inhabited by several thousand refugees, was 
targeted by the ustasha artillery for two hours. Fourteen 
people were wounded in these bestial attacks by crazed 
supporters of the vampire from Grude [reference to Herceg-Bosna 
president Mate Boban]. Despite the increasing aggressor attacks 
on the free part of the Mostar municipality, the demarcation 
lines have remain unchanged and firmly controlled by the 4th 
Corps units. 

