<H3> <TI>   HVO Warns of Effects of Vitez Plant Explosion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0201171194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0201171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Croatian Defense Council's Vitez operational 
group today warned the UN Protection Forces and other 
international organizations about the consequences of a possible 
explosion of the ammunition factory in Vitez. This factory 
stores explosives and dangerous chemicals, and if it is blown up 
by the defenders or as a result of Muslim shelling everything 
within a 3 km radius would be destroyed. 
  A document issued by the Vitez operational group also warns 
that toxic gases would affect people living from 2 to 15 km from 
the factory. Snow, rain, and fog could reduce the effect of 
toxic clouds to a certain extent, but in any case the safety 
zone for the population of the area would be at least 20 km away 
from the epicenter of the explosion, the Vitez operational group 
warns in the document. 

</TEXT>

