<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidency Introduces Defense, Reconstruction Tax </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0201211294 Paris AFP in English 2048 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0201211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, Jan 2 (AFP) -- Bosnian wage earners are to 
pay 10 percent of their net income towards the costs of 
defending and rebuilding their country, Bosnian television said 
Sunday [2 January]. The new defence and reconstruction tax, 
which is effective as of this month, was agreed in a law passed 
by Bosnia's collective presidency, the television said. It will 
be levied on Bosnians living in Bosnia-Herzegovina and on 
Bosnian nationals working abroad. Observers noted were the main 
targets of the new legislation [sentence as received]. A 
presidency statement said: "Bosnian workers abroad will thus be 
able to participate in an organised way in efforts to defend the 
country." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

