<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Comments on Relations With UN Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0301194694 Pristina TVP Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0301194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pristina TVP Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic after </F>
talks with (Sergio Demel), adviser to UN Secretary General 
Butrus Butrus-Ghali, in Pale on 3 January -- recorded] 
  [Text] We have agreed that there is no animosity between 
the UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] and the Serb side, that the 
Serbs are very cooperative in that respect, but that some 
[humanitarian] convoys are being delayed because of 
irregularities in the convoys themselves. Either there is no 
permission to search the entire convoy, or there are too many 
people or things, and our soldiers abide strictly to what they 
have on their lists. We might show a bit more flexibility 
toward UNPROFOR there. However, we do have to be somewhat 
cautious since the Muslims are doubtless getting weapons and 
ammunition, that is beyond any doubt. 
  We would never accuse the UNPROFOR Command. We know that 
General Briquemont and all his officers are exceptionally 
professional and honorable soldiers, but individuals are 
probably smuggling arms for money. We have to be very cautious 
there as we do not want the war to be prolonged. 

</TEXT>

