<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hungarians Refuse To Postpone Komarno Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301203694 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
1830 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0301203694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mikulas Duray and Stefan Pasztor, representatives of 
the Hungarian minority in Slovakia, continue to refuse to 
postpone the Komarno 8 January meeting of deputies and mayors 
who are to debate the possibility of setting up in southern 
Slovakia a region with a special legal status. 
  There is no reason to change anything, Komarno Mayor Stefan 
Pasztor said in an interview with CTK. Problems remain and we 
need a joint stance of a large number of people. At the same 
time he assured that the meeting will be held in accordance with 
the law on petitions. 
  Matica Slovenska [Slovak cultural institution] officials 
yesterday appealed for the meeting in Komarno to be cancelled. 
In their opinion, the meeting endangers the territorial 
integrity of the Slovak Republic. They also demanded that a law 
on the protection of the republic be adopted. 
  Mikulas Duray reckons that it will be not possible to push 
through the demands of the Hungarian minority under the present 
government. However, he considers a Hungarian self-governing 
region, where minority Slovaks would enjoy the same status as do 
the Hungarians within the Slovak majority, on a reciprocal 
basis, to be a realistic long-term objective. 

</TEXT>

