<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatian, B-H Leaders Meet To Discuss Peace </TI></H3>
<H4>   Granic Denies Plans To Intervene </H4>
<F P=102> AU0401175794 Vienna Oesterreich Eins Radio Network in German 
1700 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0401175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna Oesterreich Eins Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Elisa Wasch] </F>
  [Excerpt] [Announcer] In Vienna talks about Bosnia have 
started today again, for the second time in three weeks. The 
meeting between Bosnian Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic and 
Croatian Foreign Minister Mate Granic will deal mainly with 
territorial issues. Elisa Wasch reports on the negotiations. 
  [Wasch] Both sides today stressed that they finally want to 
put an end to the fighting in Bosnia-Herzegovina. Over the past 
months, the Muslim government units in central Bosnia managed to 
conquer six towns; about 70,000 Croats are surrounded there. As 
a result, over the past days threats have come from Zagreb. 
Both President Tudjman and Defense Minister Susak spoke of a 
potential Croatian military intervention in Bosnia if the 
Muslims do not cease their offensive. Croatian Foreign Minister 
Mate Granic, who participated in today's talks, denies that 
there are any plans for a Croatian intervention. 
  [Begin Granic recording, in English with superimposed German 
translation] We do not have any plan to make a military 
intervention. We will talk about how we can put an end to the 
fighting, about a cease-fire, and about future relations between 
Croats and Muslims. [end recording] 
  In addition, Granic said that Croatia continues to be 
willing 
to negotiate access to the Adriatic Sea, which is demanded by 
the Muslims. However, Zagreb no longer wants to talk about the 
Adriatic port of Neum, which the Muslims want to have. 
  [Being Granic recording] Croatia is ready to discuss access 
to the sea but not Neum. [end recording] 
  The Vienna talks are still going on and will be continued 
tomorrow. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-49039 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu003aa_94002" </HT>


