<H3> <TI>   U.S. Diplomats To Visit Warsaw Before Summit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401182094 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1629 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401182094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 4 Jan -- Madeleine Albright, President Bill 
Clinton's special envoy, will arrive in Poland on 7 January. 
The visit by the American delegation is to take place a few 
days before the NATO summit in Brussels, and before a meeting of 
the Visegrad Group leaders with President Bill Clinton, a 
Foreign Ministry Press Department statement received by PAP 
today says. Madeleine Albright is the U.S. permanent 
representative to the United Nations and a member of the 
cabinet. Among members of the delegation is General John 
Shalikashvili, head of the joint chiefs of staffs of the U.S. 
Armed Forces. "The delegation will held a number of high level 
meetings," the statement says. As a PAP journalist has learned 
from a reliable source, it can be expected that the delegation 
will be received by the president and the head of government. 

